label.value: RNA polymerase IV transcription repressor complex

definition.value: A protein complex, located in the nucleus, that possesses activity that prevents or downregulates transcription from a RNA polymerase IV promoter.

label.value: RNA polymerase V transcription repressor complex

definition.value: A protein complex, located in the nucleus, that possesses activity that prevents or downregulates transcription from a RNA polymerase V promoter.

label.value: RNA polymerase II transcription factor complex

definition.value: A transcription factor complex that acts at promoters of genes transcribed by RNA polymerase II.

label.value: RNA polymerase III transcription factor complex

definition.value: A transcription factor complex that acts at promoters of genes transcribed by RNA polymerase III.

label.value: RNA polymerase IV transcription factor complex

definition.value: A transcription factor complex that acts at promoters of genes transcribed by RNA polymerase IV.

label.value: RNA polymerase V transcription factor complex

definition.value: A transcription factor complex that acts at promoters of genes transcribed by RNA polymerase V.

label.value: phosphodiesterase activity, acting on 3'-phosphoglycolate-terminated DNA strands

definition.value: Catalysis of the hydrolytic removal of phosphoglycolate from the 3'-terminus of a 3'-phosphoglycolate-terminated oligonucleotides.

Catalysis of the reaction -  L-lysine + acetyl-CoA -eq- N6-acetyl-L-lysine + CoA + H(+).
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing alpha-linked alpha-D-glucose residue with release of alpha-D-glucose.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing alpha-(1--gt-3)-linked alpha-D-glucose residues with release of alpha-D-glucose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cyclic adenosine monophosphate + H2O -eq- cyclic inosine monophosphate + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5'deoxyadenosine + H2O -eq- 5'deoxyinosine + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5'methyl thioadenosine + H2O -eq- 5'methyl thioinosine + NH3.

Either of the ends of a meiotic spindle, a spindle that forms as part of meiosis, where spindle microtubules are organized -  usually contains a microtubule organizing center and accessory molecules, spindle microtubules and astral microtubules.

An anaphase promoting complex bound to the \'fizzy family\' APC activator Cdc20|Slp1 which\nregulates the metaphase anaphase transition by activating the APC|C to target the anaphase inhibitor securin and promotes sister chromatid separation.

An anaphase promoting complex bound to the \'fizzy-related family\' APC activator FZR1|Cdh1|Srw1 that regulates mitotic exit by activating the APC|C to target mitotic cyclins for destruction during anaphase and telophase. Is also active during G1.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any ceramide, a class of lipids that is composed of sphingosine linked to a fatty acid. Ceramides are a major component of cell membranes.
The portion of the mitochondrial inner membrane that is not invaginated to form cristae. The inner boundary membrane lies parallel to the outer membrane.

Combining with an adipokinetic hormone to initiate a change in cell activity. Adipokinetic hormones (AKHs) are peptide hormones that are involved in the mobilization of sugar and lipids from the insect fat body during energy-requiring activities such as flight and locomotion. They also contribute to hemolymph sugar homeostasis.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an adipokinetic hormone. Adipokinetic hormones (AKHs) are peptide hormones that are involved in the mobilization of sugar and lipids from the insect fat body during energy-requiring activities such as flight and locomotion. They also contribute to hemolymph sugar homeostasis.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an adipokinetic hormone receptor. Adipokinetic hormones (AKHs) are peptide hormones that are involved in the mobilization of sugar and lipids from the insect fat body during energy-requiring activities such as flight and locomotion. They also contribute to hemolymph sugar homeostasis.

Catalysis of the reaction -  (EE)-geranyllinalool + NADPH + O2 -eq- 4,8,12-trimethyl-1,3,7,11-tridecatetraene + NADP+ + 2 H2O. It is unknown whether this reaction proceeds by the direct release of the 4-carbon compound but-1-en-3-one, or whether the substrate is first degraded to C18-farnesylacetone and then cleaved to produce 4,8,12-trimethyl-1,3,7,11-tridecatetraene (TMTT) and acetone.

Catalysis of the reaction -  (E)-nerolidol + NADPH + O2 -eq- (3E)-4,8-dimethylnona-1,3,7-triene + NADP+ + 2 H2O. It is unknown whether this reaction proceeds by the direct release of the 4-carbon compound but-1-en-3-one, or whether the substrate is first degraded to C11-geranylacetone and then cleaved to produce (3E)-4,8-dimethylnona-1,3,7-triene (DMNT) and acetone.
The volume enclosed by the membrane of a phagocytic vesicle.
All of the contents of a cilium, excluding the plasma membrane surrounding the cilium.
All of the contents of a bacterial-type flagellum, excluding the plasma membrane surrounding the flagellum.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a L27 domain of a protein. L27 is composed of conserved negatively charged amino acids and a conserved aromatic amino acid. L27 domains can assemble proteins involved in signaling and establishment and maintenance of cell polarity into complexes by interacting in a heterodimeric manner.
The binding activity of a molecule that brings together the COPII vesicle proteins and one or more other molecules, permitting them to function in a coordinated way.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-fructose-6-phosphate -eq- dihydroxyacetone + D-glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate.
A heterotrimeric protein complex formed by the association of MMP7, DLG1 and either LIN7A or LIN7C -  regulates the stability and localization of DLG1 to cell junctions.
Increases the activity of a ubiquitin-protein transferase, an enzyme that catalyzes the covalent attachment of ubiquitin to lysine in a substrate protein.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a centromere-specific nucleosome, a form of nucleosome located only at the centromere, in which the histone H3 is replaced by the variant form CENP-A (sometimes known as CenH3).

The portion of endoplasmic reticulum, the intracellular network of tubules and cisternae, that occurs near the nucleus. The lumen of the perinuclear endoplasmic reticulum is contiguous with the nuclear envelope lumen (also called perinuclear space), the region between the inner and outer nuclear membranes.

label.value: extrinsic component of fungal-type vacuolar membrane

definition.value: The component of a fungal-type vacuolar membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes that are loosely bound to one of its surfaces, but not integrated into the hydrophobic region.

label.value: replication fork progression beyond termination site

definition.value: Regulation of DNA replication by a mechanism that allows a DNA replication fork to progress beyond a termination site, which is a region containing fork pausing elements that influence the progression and merging of DNA replication forks.
A chromosomal region that contains fork pausing elements influencing the progression and merging of DNA replication forks.

A protein complex comprising tumor necrosis factor (TNF) receptor-associated factor 2 (TRAF2) and glutathione S-transferase pi 1 (GSTP1). This complex is thought to disrupt the TNF signaling cascade, thus down-regulating inflammatory responses.

A heterodimeric protein complex that is composed of cardiotrophin-like cytokine factor 1 (product of the CLCF1 gene) and cytokine receptor-like factor 1 (product of the CRLF gene) and is secreted into the extracellular space. The CRLF-CLCF1 complex is a ligand for the ciliary neurotrophic factor (CNTF) receptor complex.

A protein complex that is composed of two soluble ciliary neurotrophic factor receptor alpha subunits (product of the CNTFR gene) and two molecules of cardiotrophin-like cytokine factor 1 (product of the CLCF1 gene). The complex is secreted into the extracellular space.
